h5901.definition: from {{h5892}}; urbane; Iri, an Israelite; Iri.

h5902.definition: from {{h5892}}; city-wise; Iram, an Idumaean; Iram.

h5904.definition: from {{h5892}} and {{h5175}}; city of a serpent; Ir-Nachash, a place in Palestine; Irnahash.

h5905.definition: from {{h5892}} and {{h8121}}; city of the sun; Ir-Shemesh, a place in Palestine; Irshemesh.

h5906.definition: or עָשׁ; from {{h5789}}; the constellation of the Great Bear (perhaps from its migration through the heavens); Arcturus.

h5907.definition: probably for {{h5909}}; Akbor, the name of an Idumaean and of two Israelites; Achbor.

h5908.definition: probably from an unused root in the literal sense of entangling; a spider (as weaving a network); spider.

h5909.definition: probably from the same as {{h5908}} in the secondary sense of attacking; a mouse (as nibbling); mouse.

h5910.definition: apparently from an unused root meaning to hem in; Akko (from its situation on a bay); Accho.

h5911.definition: from {{h5916}}; troubled; Akor, the name of a place in Palestine; Achor.

h5912.definition: from an unused root meaning to trouble; troublesome; Akan, an Israelite; Achan. Compare {{h5917}}.

h5913.definition: a primitive root; properly, to tie, specifically, with fetters; but used only as denominative from {{h5914}}; to put on anklets; make a tinkling ornament.

h5914.definition: from {{h5913}}; a fetter; hence, an anklet; stocks, tinkling ornament.

h5915.definition: feminine of {{h5914}}; anklet; Aksah, an Israelitess; Achsah.

h5916.definition: a primitive root; properly, to roil water; figuratively, to disturb or affict; trouble, stir.

h5917.definition: from {{h5916}}; troublesome; Akar, an Israelite; Achar. Compare {{h5912}}.

h5918.definition: from {{h5916}}; muddler; Okran, an Israelite; Ocran.

h5919.definition: probably from an unused root meaning to coil; an asp (from lurking coiled up); adder.

h5920.definition: from {{h5927}}; properly, the top; specifically, the Highest (i.e. God); also (adverb) aloft, to Jehovah; above, high, most High.

h5921.definition: properly, the same as {{h5920}} used as a preposition (in the singular or plural often with prefix, or as conjunction with a particle following); above, over, upon, or against (yet always in this last relation with a downward aspect) in a great variety of applications; above, according to(-ly), after, (as) against, among, and, × as, at, because of, beside (the rest of), between, beyond the time, × both and, by (reason of), × had the charge of, concerning for, in (that), (forth, out) of, (from) (off), (up-) on, over, than, through(-out), to, touching, × with.

h5922.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5921}}; about, against, concerning, for, (there-) fore, from, in, × more, of, (there-, up-) on, (in-) to,   why with.

h5923.definition: or עוֹל; from {{h5953}}; a yoke (as imposed on the neck), literally or figuratively; yoke.

h5925.definition: feminine of {{h5923}}; burden; Ulla, an Israelite; Ulla.

h5926.definition: from an unused root meaning to stutter; stuttering; stammerer.

h5927.definition: a primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative; arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up,   shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, × mention, mount up, offer, make to pay,   perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.

h5928.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5930}}; a holocaust; burnt offering.

h5929.definition: from {{h5927}}; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage; branch, leaf.

h5930.definition: or עוֹלָה; feminine active participle of {{h5927}}; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke); ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also {{h5766}}.

h5931.definition: (Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to {{h5927}}; a pretext (as arising artificially); occasion.

h5933.definition: or עַליָה; the same as {{h5932}}; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean; Aliah, Alvah.

h5934.definition: passive participle of {{h5956}} in the denominative sense of {{h5958}}; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor; youth.

h5935.definition: or עַלְיָן; from {{h5927}}; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean; Alian, Alvan.

h5936.definition: feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech; horse-leech.

h5937.definition: a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult; be joyful, rejoice, triumph.

h5939.definition: feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk; dark, twilight.

h5941.definition: from {{h5927}}; lofty; Eli, an Israelite highpriest; Eli.

h5944.definition: feminine from {{h5927}}; something lofty, i.e. a stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky; ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour.

h5945.definition: from {{h5927}}; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme; (Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most).

h5946.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5945}}; the Supreme; Most high.

h5948.definition: from {{h5953}} in the sense of completing; probably a crucible (as working over the metal); furnace.

h5949.definition: or עֲלִלָה; from {{h5953}} in the sense of effecting; an exploit (of God), or a performance (of man, often in a bad sense); by implication, an opportunity; act(-ion), deed, doing, invention, occasion, work.

h5952.definition: from {{h5927}}; a second-story room; chamber. Compare {{h5944}}.

h5953.definition: a primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal); abuse, affect, × child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).

h5954.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5953}} (in the sense of thrusting oneself in),; to enter; causatively, to introduce; bring in, come in, go in.

h5955.definition: feminine active participle of {{h5953}}; only in plural gleanings; by extension gleaning-time; (gleaning) (of the) grapes, grapegleanings.

h5956.definition: a primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. conceal (literally or figuratively); × any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).

h5957.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5769}}; remote time, i.e. the future or past indefinitely; often adverb, forever; for (n-)ever (lasting), old.

h5958.definition: from {{h5956}}; (compare {{h5959}}); properly, something kept out of sight, i.e. a lad; young man, stripling.

h5959.definition: feminine of {{h5958}}; a lass (as veiled or private); damsel, maid, virgin.

h5960.definition: from {{h5956}}; hidden; See also {{h5963}}.; Almon, a place in Palestine

h5961.definition: plural of {{h5959}}; properly, girls, i.e. the soprano or female voice, perhaps falsetto; Alamoth.

h5962.definition: (Aramaic) patrial from a name corresponding to {{h5867}} contracted; an Elamite or inhabitant of Elam; Elamite.

h5963.definition: from the same as {{h5960}} and the dual of {{h1960}} (compare {{h1015}}) with enclitic of direction; Almon towards Diblathajim; Almon-Diblathajemah, a place in Moab; Almondilathaim.

h5964.definition: from {{h5956}}; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites; Alameth, Alemeth.

h5965.definition: a primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. exult, wave joyously; × peacock, rejoice, solace self.

h5966.definition: a primitive root; to sip up; suck up.

h5968.definition: a primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid; faint, overlaid, wrap self.

h5969.definition: from {{h5968}}; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning; fainted.

h5970.definition: a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult; be joyful, rejoice, triumph.

h5971.definition: from {{h6004}}; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock; folk, men, nation, people.

h5973.definition: from {{h6004}}; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. in conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English); accompanying, against, and, as (× long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of, (un-) to, with(-al).

h5974.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5973}}; by, from, like, to(-ward), with.

h5975.definition: a primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive); abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair,   serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-) stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.

h5976.definition: for {{h4571}}; to shake; be at a stand.

h5977.definition: from {{h5975}}; a spot (as being fixed); place, (  where) stood, upright.

h5978.definition: prolonged for {{h5973}}; along with; against, by, from, + me, + mine, of, + that I take, unto, upon, with(-in.)

h5979.definition: from {{h5975}}; a station, i.e. domicile; standing.

h5980.definition: from {{h6004}}; conjunction, i.e. society; mostly adverb or preposition (with prepositional prefix), near, beside, along with; (over) against, at, beside, hard by, in points.

h5981.definition: the same as {{h5980}}; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine; Ummah.

h5982.definition: or עַמֻּד; from {{h5975}}; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. platform; × apiece, pillar.

h5983.definition: from {{h5971}}; tribal, i.e. inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country; Ammon, Ammonites.

h5984.definition: patronymically from {{h5983}}; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish; Ammonite(-s).

h5986.definition: from {{h6006}}; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet; Amos.

h5987.definition: from {{h6009}}; deep; Amok, an Israelite; Amok.

h5988.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h410}}; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites; Ammiel.

h5989.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h1935}}; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites; Ammihud.

h5990.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h2064}}; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite; Ammizabad.

h5991.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h2353}}; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince; Ammihud (from the margin).

h5992.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h5068}}; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites; Amminadab.

h5993.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h5081}}; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite; Amminadib.

h5994.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6012}}; profound, i.e. unsearchable; deep.

h5995.definition: from {{h6014}}; a bunch of grain; handful, sheaf.

h5996.definition: from {{h5971}} and {{h7706}}; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite; Ammishaddai.

h5997.definition: from a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man; another, fellow, neighbour.

h5998.definition: a primitive root; to toil, i.e. work severely and with irksomeness; (take) labour (in).

h5999.definition: from {{h5998}}; toil, i.e. wearing effort; hence, worry, whether of body or mind; grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness.

h6000.definition: the same as {{h5999}}; Amal, an Israelite; Amal.
